<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5201929>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Heleomyzinae, locomotory spicules, across mid-ventral zone of the posterior margin of the second and the anterior half of the third abdominal segment, uppermost vertical line indicates the mid-ventral point, horizontal line indicates approximate segment boundary, (A) Eccoptomera microps, (B) Scoliocentra brachypterna, (C) Heleomyza borealis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5201929/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5201921>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Heleomyzidae, anterior spiracles, lateral view, scale bar 0.1 mm, fan shape: (A) Eccoptomera microps, (B) Scoliocentra brachypterna; transverse rosette shape: (C) Heleomyza borealis, (D) Tephrochlamys flavipes, (E) Tephrochlamys tarsalis, (F) Heteromyza rotundicornis; rosette shape: (G) Suillia variegata, (H) Suillia laevifrons, and (I) Suillia ustulata." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5201921/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5201925>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Heleomyzinae and Heteromyzinae, posterior spiracles, apical view, scale bar 0.1 mm, Heleomyzinae: (A) Eccoptomera microps, (B) Scoliocentra brachypterna, (C) Heleomyza borealis; Heteromyzinae: (D) Tephrochlamys flavipes, (E) Tephrochlamys tarsalis, (F) Heteromyza rotundicornis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5201925/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5201937>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Heleomyzinae, head skeletons, left hand figures, whole structure, lateral view, mandible to the right, right hand figures, dorsal view of intermediate sclerite and mandible in that order, scale bar 0.25 mm, (A, B) Eccoptomera microps, (C, D) Scoliocentra brachypterna, (E, F) Heleomyza borealis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5201937/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

